import pandas as pd
from pyecharts.charts import Bar, Page, Pie, Line

df = pd.read_csv('C:/Users/admin/Desktop//20192.csv',encoding='utf-8', delimiter="\t", error_bad_lines=False)

counts = { }        
for x in df["trade"]:         
    if  x in counts:
        counts[x] += 1
    else:
        counts[x] = 1

trade=[]
for y in counts.keys():
    trade.append(y)
trade_values=[]
for z in counts.values():
    trade_values.append(z)

from pyecharts import options as opts
def pie_radius() -> Pie:
    c = (
        Pie()
        .add(
            "",
            [list(z) for z in zip(trade, trade_values)],
            radius=["50%", "75%"],
        )
        .set_global_opts(
            title_opts=opts.TitleOpts(title="2019"),
            legend_opts=opts.LegendOpts(orient="vertical", pos_top="100%", pos_left="10%"
            )
        )
        .set_series_opts(label_opts=opts.LabelOpts(formatter="{b}: {c}"))
    )
    return c
pie_radius().render_notebook()

from pyecharts import options as opts
from pyecharts.globals import ChartType, SymbolType
from pyecharts.charts import Bar,Tab,Line,Map,Timeline,Grid,Scatter
import pandas as pd
import csv, os

data = pd.read_csv('C:/Users/admin/Desktop//.csv',encoding='gbk') 

def _map()->Timeline:#,
    c=Timeline()
    for i in range(2013,2018):
        map=(
            Map()
            .add("",list(zip(list(data.),list(data["{}".format(i)]))),"china",is_map_symbol_show=False)
            .set_global_opts(
                title_opts=opts.TitleOpts(title="{}".format(i),subtitle="",subtitle_textstyle_opts=opts.TextStyleOpts(color="blue",font_size=18)),
                visualmap_opts=opts.VisualMapOpts(min_= 6000, max_=43351,series_index=0)
            )

        )
        c.add(map,"{}".format(i))
    return c

import pandas as pd
from pyecharts.charts import Map
from pyecharts import options as opts
from pyecharts.globals import ChartType, SymbolType

df = pd.read_csv('C:/Users/admin/Desktop//movie2.csv',encoding='utf-8', delimiter="\t", error_bad_lines=False)

counts = { }        
for x in df["pname"]:         
    if  x in counts:
        counts[x] += 1
    else:
        counts[x] = 1
        
province=[]
for y in counts.keys():
    province.append(y)
province_values=[]
for z in counts.values():
    province_values.append(z)

def map_() -> Map:
    c = (
        Map()
        .add("",[list(z) for z in zip(province, province_values)], "china")
        .set_global_opts(
            
            title_opts=opts.TitleOpts(title=""),
            visualmap_opts=opts.VisualMapOpts(max_=110),
        )
    )
    return c

 = map_()
